cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing user-generated content to measure urban deprivation, which involves social networks and information extraction. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a new method to automatically mine deprivation at a fine level of spatio-temporal granularity, which involves software development. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper addresses a societal issue of measuring and addressing urban deprivation. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper proposes computational methods to extract proxies of deprivation at a fine spatio-temporal level of granularity. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible category as the paper involves natural language processing techniques for thematic analysis of the outcomes.
